<task id="task-8487" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Configure email notifications in TestOps</title><shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc "><ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-testops" class="- topic/ph "/> sends notification emails to help you keep track of scheduled test runs. You can receive notification emails when test runs are uploaded to <ph conkeyref="name-variables/testops" class="- topic/ph "/>.</shortdesc><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context "><p class="- topic/p ">You can  receive the following email notifications:</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">Notifications on test runs that are uploaded to <ph conkeyref="name-variables/testops" class="- topic/ph "/>.</li><li class="- topic/li ">Weekly reports based on your testing activities.</li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">To configure email notifications, follow these steps:</p></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Sign in to <xref href="https://testops.katalon.io/" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Katalon TestOps</xref>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the top left corner, click on your avatar and select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Notification Settings</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp "><image width="700" href="Image/TestOps_user_settings.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">TestOps Notification Settings dropdown</alt></image></stepxmp></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the notification page, select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Notifications</uicontrol> and configure your options.</cmd><stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp "><image width="700" href="Image/TestOps_notifications_page.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">TestOps Notifications page</alt></image></stepxmp></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result "/></taskbody></task>